cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with compressed sensing of multi-channel EEG signals, which involves signal processing, optimization, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an optimization model with L0 norm and Schatten-0 norm to enforce cosparsity and low rank structures, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories.
